Excellent. Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the notification channel formats. Based on my thorough exploration, I now have the complete picture.

---

## Notification Channel Formats - Complete Analysis

I've conducted a thorough exploration of all notification channel implementations in the Changelogue codebase. Here's the complete breakdown:

### Architecture Overview

All notification channels implement the **`Sender` interface** defined in `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/sender.go`:

```go
// Notification is the payload sent through all notification channels.
type Notification struct {
	Title   string `json:"title"`
	Body    string `json:"body"`
	Version string `json:"version"`
}

// Sender is the interface that all notification channel implementations must satisfy.
type Sender interface {
	Send(ctx context.Context, ch *models.NotificationChannel, msg Notification) error
}
```

The notification is created in the `NotifyWorker` at `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/worker.go` (lines 82-86):

```go
msg := Notification{
	Title:   fmt.Sprintf("New release: %s", release.Version),
	Body:    string(release.RawData),
	Version: release.Version,
}
```

---

### 1. **Webhook Sender** - Generic JSON

**File:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/webhook.go`

**Type:** `webhook`

**Configuration:**
```json
{
  "url": "https://example.com/webhook"
}
```

**Payload Format (most basic):**
Sends the raw `Notification` struct as JSON POST:
```json
{
  "title": "New release: v1.14.0",
  "body": "...",
  "version": "v1.14.0"
}
```

**Key Characteristics:**
- No transformation or special formatting
- Direct JSON serialization of the Notification struct
- Single POST request to configured URL
- Content-Type: `application/json`
- Simplest format - receiver must parse Body themselves

---

### 2. **Slack Sender** - Block Kit (Rich Formatting)

**File:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/slack.go`

**Type:** `slack`

**Configuration:**
```json
{
  "webhook_url": "https://hooks.slack.com/services/YOUR/WEBHOOK/URL"
}
```

**Payload Structure:**
```go
type slackPayload struct {
	Blocks []slackBlock `json:"blocks"`
}

type slackBlock struct {
	Type     string      `json:"type"`
	Text     *slackText  `json:"text,omitempty"`
	Fields   []slackText `json:"fields,omitempty"`
	Elements []slackText `json:"elements,omitempty"`
}

type slackText struct {
	Type string `json:"type"`
	Text string `json:"text"`
}
```

**Two Formatting Modes:**

#### A. Simple Fallback (non-SemanticReport messages)
```json
{
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "text": {
        "type": "plain_text",
        "text": "New release: geth v1.14.0"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "Released on GitHub with security fixes"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

#### B. Rich Semantic Report Formatting
When Body is valid JSON of a `SemanticReport`, builds multiple blocks:

```go
type SemanticReport struct {
	// SRE-focused fields
	Subject          string   `json:"subject"`
	RiskLevel        string   `json:"risk_level"`
	RiskReason       string   `json:"risk_reason"`
	StatusChecks     []string `json:"status_checks"`
	ChangelogeSummary string   `json:"changelog_summary"`
	DownloadCommands []string `json:"download_commands,omitempty"`
	DownloadLinks    []string `json:"download_links,omitempty"`

	// Existing fields
	Summary        string `json:"summary,omitempty"`
	Availability   string `json:"availability"`
	Adoption       string `json:"adoption"`
	Urgency        string `json:"urgency"`
	Recommendation string `json:"recommendation"`
}
```

**Block Composition** (`buildSemanticBlocks` function, lines 57-173):
1. **Header block** - Title
2. **Subject section** - If present, in bold markdown
3. **Risk/Urgency/Availability field section**:
   ```
   Risk Level: 🔴 HIGH
   Urgency: High
   Availability: GA
   ```
   Risk emoji mapping:
   - LOW → 🟢
   - MEDIUM → 🟡
   - HIGH → 🔴
   - CRITICAL → ⚫
   - Default → ⚪

4. **Divider + Risk Assessment section** - If RiskReason present
5. **Divider + Status Checks section** - If present (bulleted list)
6. **Divider + Changelog section** - Uses ChangelogSummary or Summary
7. **Divider + Recommendation section** - If present
8. **Adoption section** - If present
9. **Divider + Download Commands** - Code block with backticks
10. **Download Links section** - If present (angle-bracket links)
11. **Divider + Context footer** - "📡 _Sent by Changelogue_"

**Example Rich Payload:**
```json
{
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "text": {
        "type": "plain_text",
        "text": "Semantic Release Report: go-ethereum v1.16.4"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Ready to Deploy: go-ethereum v1.16.4*"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "fields": [
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*Risk Level:*\n🔴 HIGH"
        },
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*Urgency:*\nHigh"
        },
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*Availability:*\nGA"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Risk Assessment*\nVersion not found in sources"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Status Checks*\n• Binaries Unverified\n• Docker Image Unverified"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Download Commands*\n```docker pull ethereum/client-go:v1.16.4```"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Download Links*\n• <https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/releases/tag/v1.16.4>"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "context",
      "elements": [
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "📡 _Sent by Changelogue_"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

---

### 3. **Discord Sender** - Embeds

**File:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/discord.go`

**Type:** `discord`

**Configuration:**
```json
{
  "webhook_url": "https://discordapp.com/api/webhooks/YOUR/WEBHOOK"
}
```

**Payload Structure:**
```go
type discordPayload struct {
	Embeds []discordEmbed `json:"embeds"`
}

type discordEmbed struct {
	Title       string              `json:"title"`
	Description string              `json:"description"`
	Color       int                 `json:"color"`
	Fields      []discordEmbedField `json:"fields,omitempty"`
}

type discordEmbedField struct {
	Name   string `json:"name"`
	Value  string `json:"value"`
	Inline bool   `json:"inline"`
}
```

**Payload Format:**
```json
{
  "embeds": [
    {
      "title": "New release: geth v1.14.0",
      "description": "Released on GitHub with security fixes",
      "color": 5793522,
      "fields": [
        {
          "name": "Version",
          "value": "v1.14.0",
          "inline": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

**Key Characteristics:**
- Single embed per notification
- Color: `0x5865F2` (Discord blurple - hex 5793522 in decimal)
- Body text truncated to 4096 characters max (Discord limit) with "..." suffix if truncated
- Always includes Version field (inline)
- No special handling for SemanticReport - treats Body as plain text
- Much simpler than Slack (no rich semantic parsing)

---

### Data Flow Comparison

| Field | Webhook | Slack (Simple) | Slack (Semantic) | Discord |
|-------|---------|----------------|------------------|---------|
| **Title** | JSON title | Header block | Header block | Embed title |
| **Body** | JSON body | Mrkdwn section | Multiple blocks (risk, changelog, etc.) | Embed description (truncated to 4096) |
| **Version** | JSON version | Not displayed | Not displayed | Field (inline) |
| **Rich Fields** | None | None | Yes (risk emoji, fields section) | None |
| **Formatting** | None | Markdown blocks | Semantic blocks + dividers | Discord embeds |
| **Semantic Parsing** | No | No | Yes (JSON.Unmarshal check) | No |

---

### Message Creation in NotifyWorker

At `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/worker.go` (lines 58-96), the workflow is:

1. Fetch the Release from database
2. List all subscriptions for that source
3. For each subscription:
   - Fetch the NotificationChannel
   - Create a Notification with:
     - `Title`: `"New release: {version}"`
     - `Body`: `release.RawData` (raw JSON string)
     - `Version`: `release.Version`
   - Send via appropriate Sender based on `ch.Type`

---

### Key File Paths

- **Sender Interface:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/sender.go`
- **Webhook Implementation:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/webhook.go`
- **Slack Implementation:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/slack.go`
- **Discord Implementation:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/discord.go`
- **Notification Worker:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/worker.go`
- **Models (SemanticReport):** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/models/semantic_release.go`
- **Tests:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/routing/*_test.go`

